A vintage 1960s travel poster style illustration depicting a futuristic conference hall in Orlando, Florida, with art deco palm trees framing a grand modernist auditorium. Inside, stylized retro-futuristic computer terminals display swirling data connections represented as colorful geometric ribbons flowing between different shaped nodes - cubes, spheres, and cylinders - symbolizing diverse database systems connecting harmoniously. The color palette features warm oranges, teals, and cream tones with halftone dot patterns typical of mid-century printing. A dramatic sunburst radiates from behind the auditorium, suggesting excitement and innovation. The scene conveys anticipation and technical knowledge-sharing without showing any people directly, focusing instead on the architectural grandeur and abstract data visualization elements floating above elegant podiums.
